  "notes": "Choctaw (Chahta anumpa) — Muskogean language of Oklahoma and Mississippi, written in the Latin script. This spec follows the modern Mississippi Choctaw orthography: three vowel qualities a i o, short vs. long (long written doubled, aa ii oo, or with a macron), plus nasalised vowels (written with an underline/ogonek, e.g. a̱ i̱ o̱) that are not mapped here. ⟨lh⟩ is the voiceless lateral fricative /ɬ/, ⟨ch⟩ = /tʃ/, ⟨sh⟩ = /ʃ/. ⟨e⟩, ⟨u⟩ and ⟨v⟩ belong to the older Byington/missionary spelling still met in print (⟨v⟩ = /ə/); they are given here for compatibility. Glottal stop is phonemic but not consistently written.",
